{
  "texts": [
    "As it is shown in Fig. 7, the NPCR approach learns essay representation by comparing the input essay with sample essays.",
    "This is achieved by employing neural pairwise ranking model that learns both order information and relative semantic representation.",
    "The semantic representation is the difference between BERT representation of the input and reference essays, defined as relative scores.",
    "The predicted score is then obtained by averaging the sum of the relative scores and the reference score.",
    "NPCR uses a multi-sample voting strategy to determine the final score."
  ]
}